Program: Omnibus
Title: In the Wake of Colmcille
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p0376lk1
Last Broadcast Date: 26 August 1997
In a spirit of religious co-operation a crew of Catholics and Protestants attempt to recreate the 130 mile journey made by St Colmcille in 1563 when he sailed from Derry in Ireland to the Scottish island of Iona in a currach rowing boat.